{"title":"Monopolized organ collection","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/872275382/0/marginalrevolution~Monopolized-organ-collection.html","date":1709019546000,"content":"<div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>The nation’s 56 organ procurement organizations collect organs — mainly kidneys — from deceased donors at hospitals and arrange for them to be transported to surgeons at the 250 U.S. medical centers that perform transplants. Each procurement group holds a government-guaranteed monopoly over a swath of U.S. territory where it operates.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>Some have failed for years to collect enough organs<b> </b>to meet demand, according to government records. But the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services, the part of HHS that licenses the nonprofits to operate, has <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/despite-low-performance-organ-collection-group-gets-new-federal-contract/2019/02/04/9b9ba2aa-2895-11e9-b2fc-721718903bfc_story.html?itid=lk_inline_manual_14\" target=\"_blank\">never decertified one</a>. In response to critiques, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.washingtonpost.com/health/2024/02/05/organ-transplants-pancreas/?itid=lk_inline_manual_14\" target=\"_blank\">the CMS issued new benchmarks</a> that will allow the agency to weed out poor performers beginning in 2026.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>Now many of these organ collection groups are <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.washingtonpost.com/health/2024/02/26/organ-transplant-investigation/\" target=\"_blank\">under investigation for fraud and overbilling the government</a>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/02/monopolized-organ-collection.html\">Monopolized organ collection</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/872275382/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/872275382/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/872275382/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/872275382/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/x.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/19/872275382/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/email20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/20/872275382/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/rss20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/02/monopolized-organ-collection.html#comments\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/comments20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/02/monopolized-organ-collection.html/feed\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/commentsrss20.png\" /></a> \r\n<div><a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/02/monopolized-organ-collection.html#comments\"><h3>Comments</h3></a><ul><li><a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/02/monopolized-organ-collection.html#comment-160723160\">There would be no fraud or overbilling involving the ...</a> <i>by If we had a free market in organs</i></li></ul></div><h3>Related Stories</h3><ul><li><a href=\"https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/02/access-to-medical-data-saves-lives.html?utm_source=rss&amp;utm_medium=rss&amp;utm_campaign=access-to-medical-data-saves-live